# GabIoT Connect Cursor Rules

## Project Context
GabIoT Connect is a secure IoT dashboard for monitoring sensor data with AI-driven analysis.
It uses React, Tailwind CSS, Supabase for backend, and Gemini for AI.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: React 19, Vite, Tailwind CSS 4, Lucide React, Recharts, Motion.
- **Backend**: Supabase (Auth, Database).
- **AI**: Google Gemini API (@google/genai).

## Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript for all files.
- Use functional components and hooks.
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling.
- Follow the established "cyber-dashboard" aesthetic (dark theme, green/cyan accents, monospace fonts).
- Implement robust error handling for all API calls and data fetching.
- Use the `showToast` system for user feedback.

## Supabase Integration
- Use the Supabase client from `src/services/supabase.ts`.
- Prefer Supabase Auth for user management.
- Store sensor telemetry in Supabase Database.

## AI Integration
- Use the Gemini service from `src/services/gemini.ts`.
- Always provide live sensor context to the AI when relevant.

## File Structure
- `src/components/`: Reusable UI components.
- `src/services/`: External service integrations (Gemini, Supabase).
- `src/App.tsx`: Main application logic and layout.
- `src/index.css`: Global styles and Tailwind configuration.
